ery asana he taught.";i:2;s:133:"Yoga anatomy expert Leslie Kaminoff describes the action and muscle engagement that occurs during this challenging full-body posture.";i:3;s:122:"Chair pose is a symmetrical standing pose in which your knees are bent and your weight is distributed evenly in your feet.";i:4;s:57:"Your spine is lifted and your arms are extended overhead.";i:5;s:113:"In this video we explore the alignment of the pelvis spine and knees in parivrtta utkatasana revolved chair pose.";i:6;s:274:"We revisit some of the themes presented in other recent videos that weve posted about rotated postures eg the benefits of maintaining a neutral spine and allowing the pelvis to follow the lumbar spine during twists but with specific cues that pertain to revolved chair pose.";i:7;s:134:"The inner thigh muscles known as the adductors will be contracting as the knees in this pose have a tendency to try and open outwards.";i:8;s:145:"You will feel a contraction in the hamstrings quads and glute muscles their job is to strengthen and help root the entire posture and prevent it.";i:9;s:23:"Your Mind Body Academy.";i:10;s:117:"This pose is also called the Chair pose just because the posture resembles like one is sitting on an invisible chair.";i:11;s:66:"This pose is one of the first pose in the Sun Salutation B series.";i:12;s:146:"It needs ample strength with the quadricep muscles to help your hips get the right support and give the knees a comfort to hold the pose for long.";i:13;s:130:"Working on the alignment of the hips along with the knees and the pelvic region is very essential to get comfortable in this pose.";i:14;s:162:"Anatomy and Alignment in Yoga Chair Pose Getting into more detailed solutions one that I am currently working with is activating the sides of the thighs and hips.";i:15;s:146:"The muscles activated can include the vastus lateralis side of the thighs gluteus minimus gluteus medius and tensor fascae latae side of the hips.";i:16;s:67:"Lift your ches